# 1. 今はできることから

Teacher: Ah, excellent work. Then, on to the next page...
An: I've made my decision...
An: I'm done wondering.
An: We're going to surpass RAD WEEKEND and show you guys what things look like from on top of the world!
Kohane: (I can still feel that fire burning right here...)
Kohane: (I want to see what it's like. Beyond Nagi and her team's dream... With An. With everyone.)
Kohane: ...
Taiga: Now do you understand? This is what you're all up against.
Kohane: (The way Taiga sang really was unbelievable...)
Kohane: (I was so shaken that I couldn't even sing...)
Kohane: (It'll take more than just skill to surpass RAD WEEKEND. But we still need to reach his level... Otherwise, I'm afraid that we won't be able to get anywhere...)
Kohane: (How do we overcome this hurdle...? No, more like an impossibly high wall...)
Kohane: (At the same time, we know we can't let that get us down.)
Kohane: (Because we've already made our decision...!)
An: Let's do it. This is our real starting point.
An: We're gonna get even better. We're gonna get Arata, Kotaro and EVER back...!
An: And surpass RAD WEEKEND!
Akito, Kohane & Toya: Yeah! Okay! Yes!
An: So, I guess we need to start discussing what to do next.
Toya: Yes, I agree. Starting with...
Toya: What do we need to do to put on an event that can surpass RAD WEEKEND?
Toya: Or rather, what specific steps can we take to make that a reality?
Akito: Yeah, right...
Akito: It's not just about having the skills to do it. We need to form strong connections not just between us, but also with the crowd. I thought I already understood that, but...
Kohane: It was her swan song.
Toya: Yes, Nagi's swan song... She was so loved by the people of this city.
Akito: I still have no idea how we're gonna top that...
Akito: But I finally understand why that event was as mind-blowing as it was...
Akito: And we're standing here today because that night happened. That's as true as it's ever been.
An: Yeah...
An: I guess we just gotta start checking off each box.
An: Because right now, we don't have the skills or the friends we'll need.
An: We'll have to face those shortcomings... And think about what steps we can take, like Toya just said.
Toya: Right. We can't stop now. We need to keep trying things as we go...
Toya: Starting with...
Toya: Bringing everyone back together. Tono, Mita and all of EVER...
An: I really don't know if what we'll have to say is gonna convince them to try again...
An: But I do know for sure that we need to tell them. About Nagi, about us and about our future.
Akito: Agreed...
Akito: If they hear about why RAD WEEKEND happened, then they might just be willing to come back around again.
Akito: I don't think our chances of success are zero.
Kohane: Yeah, I agree! Plus...
Kohane: We were able to make it this far because we all pushed each other to do better.
Toya: I also believe that we should try talking to them.
Toya: However, that may be easier said than done...
Kohane: Why?
Toya: I don't mean to spoil the moment... But it's very difficult to regain lost confidence.
Toya: It was under fairly different circumstances, but I've been down that path. I sort of understand how they feel...
Toya: And why it caused them to give up.
An: Toya...
Akito: It's tough to find the will to stand back up and fight after you've convinced yourself there's no point...
Akito: I also know how that feels...
Akito: And the way he sang. He was a monster...
Kohane: (He's right. The way Taiga sang... It scared me...)
Kohane: (We couldn't hold our own against that... And even if we'd managed to, RAD WEEKEND is something even further ahead...)
Kohane: (I understand why someone would feel totally helpless after that.)
Kohane: (At the same time...)
Kohane: ...
Kohane: (I really regret what happened...)
Kohane: (If only I could sing better... If only we could've convinced the others to stay...)
Kohane: (No, stop... There's no use crying over spilled milk.)
Kohane: (Right now, we need to think about what we can do moving forward.)
An: I agree that it'll be hard for them to come back. And... I don't think there's any guarantee that us talking to them will make that happen.
An: But at the very least, I wanna tell them about what happened to Aunt Nagi...
An: No, after coming this far together, we owe it to them. They have a right to know.
Toya: Yes, I agree completely...
Toya: And there is a chance of them coming back, no matter how small.
Akito: Alright, I'll try seeing if they'd be willing to sit down and talk with us somewhere.
An: Okay. Thanks, Akito.
An: That just leaves our giant skill gap.
Toya: To be honest, I doubt we're going to find the solution to this problem anytime soon either...
Akito: Yeah... It's not something we can fix here and now, anyway. This is gonna take us a while to figure out.
An: We wouldn't be wondering if we already knew the answer...
Toya: Right...
Toya: If no method is presenting itself, we'll just need to also be thinking about this issue while we continue our practices.
Toya: In that case...
Toya: Our first step should probably be to secure more time together. Would that be a problem for anyone?
Toya: That time can be used both for longer practices and for us to brainstorm our plans going forward.
Kohane: Yeah, let's do that...!
Kohane: (I also need to do what I can...)
Kohane: (I'm going to find the time and devote it all to singing!)
An: Oh, Kohane, over here!
Kohane: Thanks for waiting, everyone!
Kohane: I'm really sorry. I was asking my teacher about committee business and it ended up taking longer than expected.
An: No, that's totally fine! But what committee business were you asking about...?
Kohane: Oh, so... I asked to see if there's some way for me to take care of my duties during lunch in order to give myself more time to practice.
Toya: Interesting... Seems we're all on the same wavelength.
Kohane: Huh?
Toya: Shiraishi and I also had discussions along similar lines today.
An: The other hall monitors were happy to hear me out. Same goes for Toya and the library committee. I didn't think it would be this easy.
Kohane: Really...?! That's great, you two!
Akito: As for me, I quit my job.
Kohane: What?! Just like that...? I didn't realize you could leave on such short notice.
Akito: Normally, I'd have to put in my two weeks... But my manager's always been rooting for us. He even heard through the grapevine how we lost to Taiga...
Akito: So, after I told him that I wanted to focus on music more, he said, “Go get 'em! I believe in you!”
Kohane: Wow... He sounds like such a nice person.
An: Oh, speaking of work...
An: I won't be helping out at the cafe for the foreseeable future.
Kohane: Wait, and your dad's okay with that...?
An: Yup. He said, “That's fine. Don't mind us.”
An: I honestly felt a little relieved...
An: I mean, whenever I see him or any of the locals, all these emotions begin stirring up inside of me...
Kohane: Oh...
An: No, wait! I'm sorry...! I don't hate them or anything for what they did!
An: My dad and I had a talk afterwards...
An: (Alright, I should probably be getting ready for bed.)
An's Father: An.
An: What is it...?
An's Father: Please give me another chance to apologize.
An's Father: I'm sorry for not telling you about Nagi passing away. I'm really sorry...
An: You better be...
An: I mean, you never let it show at all... You even said that she might come back someday...
An: You and the others were all just respecting her last wishes... Fine, I get that. Still...
An's Father: I had trouble letting go in the end...
An: ...
An's Father: You're right. Because we'd known each other since we were kids, I didn't want to disrespect her memory.
An's Father: Also, as an artist, I wanted to see what the next generation she was talking about would be capable of.
An's Father: And... I know this will sound like an excuse...
An's Father: But as your father, I didn't want you to let go of your dream...
An: ...!
An's Father: Still, my actions have caused you a lot of pain...
An's Father: Which is why I'm genuinely sorry, An...
An: ...
An: Don't think that I'm gonna forgive you just because you're apologizing...
An's Father: ...
An: Still...
An: If I knew then that she was gone...
An: I probably wouldn't have been able to sing the way I wanted...
An: Which means... I might've never met Kohane or Akito or Toya.
An: I'm not forgiving you guys for what you did.
An: But I don't regret walking this path. Not one bit...
An's Father: An...
An's Father: I'm sorry...
An's Father: And thank you...
Kohane: That really happened...?
Kohane: (Thank goodness... An and her dad had a chance to talk things out.)
Akito: Well, in any case... We have more time to sing now.
Akito: Let's do everything we can to make the most of every extra minute.
Kohane: Right! Oh, actually, Shinonome...
Akito: Hm? What's up?
Kohane: You contacted Tono and everyone the other day, right? Can you tell us what happened after that...?
Akito: Yeah, I tried contacting them... But I only heard back from Okazaki.
Akito: And he replied, “We need time to settle down and think about what just happened.”
Kohane: I see...
An: Then, we'll just have to keep trying with Arata and the others as we go! For now, let's focus on practicing!
An: We're gonna warm up a little and then head over to MEIKO's place, right?
Toya: Yes. I know everyone there's already done quite a bit for us lately, but we should go ask to see if we can borrow her cafe again...
